wikipedia_page.main: Bobby Colvin (5 December 1876 – 1 October 1940) was a Scottish footballer who played as an outside right for Liverpool, Glossop North End (1898–99), New Brighton Tower, (1899-1901), Luton Town (1901–02), Queens Park Rangers (1902–03), Swindon Town (1903-04), and Carlisle United.
